text: form_vl.patient_art_no: Patient ART number/identifier. Never select or return this column for privacy
form_vl.sample_code: Human-readable sample identifier for display. Generated at lab in LIS. Possible duplicates across different testing labs
form_vl.remote_sample_code: Sample ID from Sample Tracking System (STS). Usually different from sample_code. Indicates request origin
form_vl.implementing_partner: NGO or partner supporting the facility. Links to r_implementation_partners table
form_vl.current_regimen: Patient antiretroviral therapy (ART) regimen at sample collection time
form_vl.patient_gender: Patient sex. Always refer to as "sex" not "gender" in queries and results
form_vl.is_patient_pregnant: Pregnancy status. Values: "yes"/"no". Use IFNULL as older records may be NULL
form_vl.is_patient_breastfeeding: Breastfeeding status. Values: "yes"/"no". Use IFNULL as older records may be NULL
form_vl.date_of_initiation_of_current_regimen: Date patient started current ART regimen
form_vl.vl_sample_id: Internal database ID - avoid in user queries

form_vl.facility_id: Links to facility_details table. The requesting facility/clinic which collected the sample. Never show the facility_id directly, always join to facility_details and show facility_name or facility_code

form_vl.lab_id: JOIN with facility_details.facility_id. The testing laboratory where sample was processed/tested. Never show the lab_id directly, always join to facility_details and show facility_name or facility_code
form_vl.result_value_absolute: Numeric VL count for comparisons (copies/mL). Use for threshold-based filtering
form_vl.result: Text result (number or text like "Not Detected"). Rarely used for filtering unless specific text matching needed
form_vl.vl_result_category: Clinical categorization: "suppressed" or "not suppressed". Preferred for clinical queries. Not to be used for joins.
form_vl.is_sample_rejected: Sample rejection status. Values: "yes"/"no". Use IFNULL as older records may be NULL. IFNULL(is_sample_rejected, "no") = "yes"
form_vl.specimen_type: Sample type (Plasma, DBS, Whole Blood). Links to r_vl_sample_type table
form_vl.rejection_on: Date of sample rejection if applicable
form_vl.sample_collection_date: Patient sample collection date. Different from request_created_datetime
form_vl.sample_dispatched_datetime: Dispatch timestamp from requesting facility to lab
form_vl.patient_has_active_tb: Active tuberculosis status. Values: "yes"/"no". Use IFNULL as older records may be NULL
form_vl.sample_tested_datetime: Lab testing timestamp. Primary date for temporal analysis
form_vl.result_value_log: Log-transformed VL result for statistical analysis
form_vl.result_status: Test result status. Links to r_sample_status table
form_vl.tested_by: Testing technician. Links to user_details table via user_id
form_vl.approved_by: Approving supervisor. Links to user_details table via user_id
form_vl.reviewed_by: Reviewing supervisor. Links to user_details table via user_id
form_vl.revised_by: Revising supervisor. Links to user_details table via user_id
form_vl.source_of_request: Request origin: LIS, STS, or API (EMR/DHIS2). Use to filter by source system
form_vl.system_patient_code: Internal patient identifier - NEVER SELECT for privacy
form_vl.last_modified_by: Last modifier user ID. Links to user_details table via user_id

form_vl.instrument_id: Testing machine/analyzer/instrument identifier. Links to instrument_machines table or instruments table. Never return instrument_id, always make sure you return the instrument_machines.config_machine_name or instruments.machine_name

form_vl.vl_test_platform: Testing machine/analyzer/instrument name. DO NOT USE THIS FOR JOINS. Always join on instrument_id to get the machine name. Only use this column as fallback to show name if instrument_id join not possible
facility_details.facility_code: Facility code identifier - prefer over facility_name for identification
facility_details.facility_state_id: State|Province. Links to geographical_divisions where geographical_divisions.geo_id = facility_details.facility_state_id
facility_details.facility_district_id: District|County. Links to geographical_divisions where geographical_divisions.geo_id = facility_details.facility_district_id
user_details.role_id: User role. Links to roles table
batch_details.lab_id: Testing laboratory. Links to facility_details table
Counting records by categorical breakdowns // SELECT category_column, COUNT(*) as count FROM table WHERE conditions GROUP BY category_column

meta.pattern: SELECT category_column, COUNT(*) as count FROM table WHERE conditions GROUP BY category_column
meta.example: SELECT vl_result_category, COUNT(*) as test_count FROM form_vl WHERE sample_tested_datetime >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 6 MONTH) GROUP BY vl_result_category

text: Analyzing trends over time // SELECT DATE_FORMAT(date_column, "%Y-%m") as month, COUNT(*) as count FROM table GROUP BY month ORDER BY month

meta.pattern: SELECT DATE_FORMAT(date_column, "%Y-%m") as month, COUNT(*) as count FROM table GROUP BY month ORDER BY month
meta.example: SELECT DATE_FORMAT(sample_tested_datetime, "%Y-%m") as test_month, COUNT(*) as monthly_tests FROM form_vl GROUP BY test_month ORDER BY test_month

text: Comparing metrics across facilities // SELECT f.facility_name, COUNT(t.*) as metric FROM table t JOIN facility_details f ON t.facility_id = f.facility_id GROUP BY f.facility_id

meta.pattern: SELECT f.facility_name, COUNT(t.*) as metric FROM table t JOIN facility_details f ON t.facility_id = f.facility_id GROUP BY f.facility_id
meta.example: SELECT f.facility_name, COUNT(v.*) as vl_tests FROM form_vl v JOIN facility_details f ON v.facility_id = f.facility_id GROUP BY f.facility_id
